               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-215" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-215" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-215" type="surname" value="PEARKES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-215" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE PEARKES</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner was my errand-boy. On the 7th of October I gave him 18<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., being the difference of a sovereign which Mr. Milner had sent to me, to pay for some ginger-beer, about five or</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183611280041"></xptr>
               <p>six o'clock in the evening—I never saw him afterwards till the 21st, when I apprehended him in Cloth-fair.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> My father has paid some of the money. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I received 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. before I took him into custody—the father worked for me, and allowed me to stop 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. a week, but with the understanding that I was to prosecute the boy as soon as he was taken, as he was such a bad boy.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
